INSERT INTO `assistance` (`id`, `category`, `device-id`, `title`, `answer`, `service-id`) VALUES
(1, 'Device', 29, 'How to reset Router', '	<p>There is a difference between <b>resetting</b> a router and <b>rebooting</b> a router. When you reboot your router that means you cycle the power to it. Resetting your router involves changing it back to its factory settings.</p>\r\n<p>Perhaps you have forgotten the password to your router and now you want to reset the password. First you need to reset the router back to its factory settings then you can use the default password to access your router.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>How to Reboot your Router</h2> \r\n<p><b>Rebooting</b> a router means <b>cycling the power</b> to it. If you want to <b>reboot</b> your router, follow these steps:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Unplug the <b>power connector</b> from the back of the router and plug it back in.</li>\r\n	<li>Wait about <b>30 seconds</b> for the router to <b>reboot</b>.</li>\r\n	<li>Your internet connection will drop when your router is rebooted. If someone is using a computer on your network to access the internet, you may want to warn them.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>How to Reset Your Router</h2>\r\n<p>When you <b>reset</b> your router the following <b>settings are changed</b>:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><b>Router</b> username and password</li>\r\n	<li><b>Wi-Fi</b> username and password</li>\r\n	<li><b>ISP</b> username and password</li>\r\n	<li>Any <b>portforwards</b> you have set up</li>\r\n	<li>Any <b>firewall</b> settings you have made</li>\r\n	<li>Basically, any configuration changes that you have made to your router.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>As you can probably tell from the list above, <b>resetting</b> your router is serious business. Proceed with caution.</p>', -1),
(2, 'Device', 5, 'Reboot your phone', 'To reboot your phone switch it off', -1),
(3, 'Device', -1, 'Get help about your phone', 'How do i replace a lost,stolen or damaged phone?\r\n\r\nIf your phone is insured with CIM Covered, youâ€™ll need to make a claim\r\n\r\nDepending on how long you have left before your agreement ends, you might be eligible to upgrade early (which may involve a cost).Contact us to discuss your options.\r\n\r\nAlternatively, take a look at our range of great value Pay as you go phones', -1),
(4, 'Device', -1, 'Line Management', 'How can I reset my Cim router?\r\nYou can do this by using the reset button on the back of your router. Take a look at the Simple setup guide that came with your router for more details. Also check your product router website to see many instructions to do the reset. Normally the reset button is on the back of your router as image shows. ', -1),
(5, 'Services', -1, 'How do I make a complaint ', '<p> If youâ€™re unhappy and want to make a complaint, our customer service team is here to help. Contact us about your problems.', -1),
(6, 'Services', -1, 'How do I set up my new SIM card', '<p>If weâ€™ve sent you a new SIM, either because youâ€™ve upgraded, or had to replace a lost or damaged SIM, youâ€™ll need to do something called a SIM swap. This is so we can link your mobile number to your SIM on our network â€“ enabling you to use your phone. So a SIM swap essentially activates your new SIM.\r\n\r\nIf you already have a new SIM, you can activate it online. Please note your SIM will only be activated if itâ€™s been ordered through your account â€“ you canâ€™t activate a SIM given to you by someone else.\r\n\r\nIf you need a new SIM get in touch</p>', -1),
(7, 'Services', -1, 'How to start a live chat with support ', '<p>You can start a Live Chat to speak to an adviser 24 hours a day, 7 days a week.\r\n\r\nThe option for Live Chat will pop up across our site and throughout our Help and Support pages. Or you can choose that option on our Contact Us page â€“ which you can use to chat with an adviser at any time.\r\n\r\nWould you like to chat with an adviser now?\r\n\r\nIf youâ€™re a business customer, you can contact our customer services team. Alternatively, you can speak with your account manager or Prime Contact if you have one.</p>', -1),
(8, 'Device', -1, 'How do I transfer photos, contacts, videos and music from my old phone to my new phone?', '<p> Upgrading or changing your phone? Find out the best ways to transfer your contacts, photos, music and videos from your old phone to your new one:\r\n\r\n<ul>Android to Android\r\n<li>If you have a Microsoft Account you can use OneDrive\r\n<li>If you have a Google Account you can use Google Drive\r\n\r\nAndroid to iOS\r\n\r\n<li>You can download the Move to iOS app from the Play Store\r\n\r\niOS to iOS\r\n\r\n<li>If youâ€™re staying with Apple you can use iCloud to transfer content\r\niOS to Android\r\n<li>If you have a Microsoft Account you can use OneDrive\r\n<li>If you have  a Google Account you can use Google Drive\r\n\r\nWindows to (Android, iOS or Windows)\r\n\r\n<li>If you have a Microsoft Account you can use OneDrive\r\n<li>If you have a Google Account you can use Google Drive</p>', -1),
