(10, 'TV&Entertainment', -1, 'tv black screen', '<p> If you can not see one or more channels and the TV screen remains black, first, restart all the equipment such as modems, cable box, PC or mobile devices.\r\n\r\nIf you use a decoder control cable connections to power and check that the connection to the Ethernet network cable between the modem and decoder is correct and working. Also check that your fiber or ADSL connection is active and that the wires are inserted into the telephone wall jack.\r\n\r\nAfter checking the cables, we recommend that you verify the operation of Wi-Fi:\r\n\r\ncontrols receiving the Wi-Fi signal, and the signal strength on the device you are using to view the selected content\r\ntry to disconnect or disassociate all devices connected via Wi-Fi network and try to see the content with a single connected device\r\nSure, finally, which are not active on your Internet connection programs that can use the available bandwidth and generate traffic on the network, such as sharing software peer-to-peer.\r\n\r\nYou can control the speed of your Internet connection via the speed and know, so, if the bandwidth tests available on the line is adequate to the vision of the content.</p>', -1),
(11, 'TV&Entertainment', -1, 'Video problem', '<p> If the video presents the suqadrettamento problems while watching, first, restart all the equipment such as modems, cable box, PC or mobile devices.\r\n\r\nWe recommend that you verify the operation of Wi-Fi:\r\n\r\ncontrols receiving the Wi-Fi signal, and the signal strength on the device you are using to view the selected content\r\ntry to disconnect or disassociate all devices connected via Wi-Fi network and try to see the content with a single connected device\r\nSure, finally, which are not active on your Internet connection programs that can use the available bandwidth and generate traffic on the network, such as sharing software peer-to-peer and, after disabling any programs, try again to see the video.\r\n\r\nYou can control the speed of your Internet connection via the speed and know, so, if the bandwidth tests available on the line is adequate to the vision of the content.\r\n\r\nIf after all these checks, the problem persists, report a problem to Technical segnalation.</p>', -1),
(12, 'TV&Entertainment', -1, 'The audio is defective', '<p> If the video presents the audio reception problems, first, restart all the equipment such as modems, cable box, PC or mobile devices.\r\n\r\nWe recommend that you verify the operation of Wi-Fi:\r\n\r\ncontrols receiving the Wi-Fi signal, and the signal strength on the device you are using to view the selected content\r\ntry to disconnect or disassociate all devices connected via Wi-Fi network and try to see the content with a single connected device\r\nSure, finally, which are not active on your Internet connection programs that can use the available bandwidth and generate traffic on the network, such as sharing software peer-to-peer and, after disabling any programs, try again to see the video.\r\n\r\nYou can control the speed of your Internet connection via the speed and know, so, if the bandwidth tests available on the line is adequate to the vision of the content.\r\n\r\nIf after all these checks, the problem persists, report a problem to Technical segnalation.</p>', -1),
(13, 'TV&Entertainment', -1, 'Some videos are stuck', '<p> Se riscontri spesso rallentamenti o blocchi e interruzione durante la visione dei contenuti video, riavvia tutti gli apparati che utilizzi come modem, decoder, pc o device mobili. \r\n\r\nTi consigliamo di verificare il funzionamento della connessione Wi-Fi:\r\n\r\ncontrolla la ricezione del segnale Wi-Fi e la potenza del segnale sul dispositivo che stai utilizzando per vedere il contenuto scelto\r\nprova a disconnettere o disassociare tutti i dispositivi collegati tramite la rete Wi-Fi e prova a vedere il contenuto con un solo dispositivo collegato\r\nAssicurati, infine, che non siano attivi sulla tua connessione Internet programmi che possono utilizzare la banda disponibile e generare traffico sulla rete, come i software di condivisione peer-to-peer e, dopo aver disabilitato eventuali programmi, prova nuovamente a vedere il video.\r\n\r\nPuoi controllare la velocitÃ  della tua connessione Internet tramite il test di velocitÃ  e sapere, cosÃ¬, se la banda disponibile sulla linea Ã¨ adeguata alla visione del contenuto.  </p>', -1),
(14, 'Services', -1, 'registration', '<p>\r\nDuring registration of your CIM Mail, you can choose the username, which is the part of the email address before the @ hypcim.it, by following the rules:\r\n\r\nMinimum of 6 and maximum of 24 characters.\r\nYou can use letters, numbers, hyphens, underscores and dots.\r\nThe first character must necessarily be a letter.\r\nThe last character must necessarily be a letter or a number.\r\nYou can not use two consecutive points.\r\n</p>', -1),
(15, 'Services', -1, 'How quickly will i get online', 'When youâ€™re in an area with a strong 4G signal, you can expect faster speeds. The number of people connected to our network at the same time also affects these speeds.\r\n\r\nCheck out our helpful hints and tips on coverage and speed', -1),
(16, 'Device', -1, 'error code 404', '<p> This is an internet error message rather than a problem with your phone. It means â€˜page not foundâ€™ - which is normally because the page youâ€™re looking for has moved or disappeared, or youâ€™ve typed in the URL wrongly.</p>', -1),
(17, 'Device', -1, 'contact service error ', '<p>This means your phone has a problem talking to our network</p>', -1),
(18, 'Family and Home', -1, 'Antivirus ', '<p>To use the antivirus security software of CIM you must have:\r\n\r\nMicrosoft Windows 8, 8.1\r\nSupport for both the 32-bit version that for the 64-bit version with:\r\n\r\n2GHz or higher\r\n2 GB of RAM for 32-bit / 4 GB of RAM for 64-bit\r\n250MB of free hard disk space\r\nMicrosoftÂ® WindowsÂ® 7\r\nSupport for both the 32-bit version that for the 64-bit version with:\r\n\r\n2GHz or higher\r\n2 GB of RAM for 32-bit / 4 GB of RAM for 64-bit\r\n250MB of free hard disk space\r\n</p>', -1),
(19, 'Family and Home', -1, 'network security', '<p>Surfing the Internet, given the ubiquity and ease of access to the network, if not done carefully, it can be the cause of undesirable events such as:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Virus infections\r\n<li>receiving unwanted email (spam)\r\n<li>invasion of privacy\r\n<li>Access credentials theft (phishing)\r\n<li>the child safety threats\r\n\r\nIf you want to avoid computer viruses remember to use and update with some continuity dedicated software such as antivirus or firewalls that are able to identify and block dangerous attack.\r\n</p>', -1),
(21, 'Device', 19, 'iPhone mail', 'To add your mail account on iPhone, tap the Settings icon from the menu:  In the Settings:  choose the voice mail, contacts, calendars then Add Account ... from the list of providers \r\nTo add your mail account on iPhone, tap the Settings icon from the menu:  In the Settings:  choose the voice mail, contacts, calendars then Add Account ... from the list of providers  touch Add account Mail fill in the fields with your details of the Alice mailbox: Name: Enter a name of your choice; Address: your full address of the domain ; Password: enter your email password; Description: Enter a name to specify this account (Home, Office, ...).', -1),
